## <a id="disabling-custom-buildpacks"></a> Deactivate custom buildpacks

You can deactivate custom buildpacks using the Elastic Application Runtime tile. In the **App Containers** pane, deselect the **Allow custom buildpacks** checkbox, as shown in the following image.<br><br>![Disable custom buildpacks](images/disable-custom-buildpacks.png)<br><br>By default, the Tanzu cf CLI gives developers the option of using a custom buildpack when they deploy apps to Elastic Application Runtime; they use the `-b` option to provide a custom buildpack URL with the `cf push` command. Deselecting the **Allow custom buildpacks** checkbox prevents the `-b` option from being used with external buildpack URLs.<br><br>For more information about custom buildpacks, see [Creating custom buildpacks](../commercial-buildpacks/custom.html).
